<br>
A bucket lay nearby, nearly filled with vomit.  Flies buzzed around the bucket, often landing to feast as flies often do.  The man would often open the door, speaking quickly, and another would enter to take the bucket away.<br>
<br>
There were times when their patient's screams kept the residents of the small village awake.  Some cursed, saying it was not their concern and to send her to the McMannus village as it was their kin while others said it was their concern because the woman put herself in danger to assist them.  Lack of sleep brings irritation, and irritation brings discontentment; a thing often avoided in small communities and very avoidable, at times.<br>
<br>
For days, the two men did what they could to help the barbarian woman.  They would drop driblets of water into her mouth, attempting to keep her hydrated.  They repeated this long, drawn-out process with broths from vegetable soups and stews, spooning only the stock into the bowl.<br>
<br>
Some members of the community banned together, demanding the woman be sent to the McMannus village.  The two men argued that she could not be moved, she was too ill still and that patience was a virtue that was needed at that time.<br>
<br>
&quot;Be damn to patience, Brother!  I know that woman and it is best to send her off before she awakens!&quot;  Eyes turned to the woman, voices demanding a name.  &quot;That is that McCulloch tart!  If you had any idea the trouble she caused for The Lion's Mane Inn-&quot;<br>
<br>
Misty Storyswapper stepped forward, holding out her hand.  &quot;Wait.  Xelita McCulloch is a member of the League, let us dispatch a letter to her to find out more about this woman before gossiping about her childhood aggressions.&quot;<br>
<br>
The two brothers agreed with the half elven bardess, and returned to their patient.  The letter was sent.<br>
<br>
Days turned to weeks and still no response, but it mattered little.  The two brothers stood over their patient, disheartened to see the distrust in her dark brown eyes. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.cox.net/bj.dailey/andora.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=1264.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=1264.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1264.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.threadControl?topicID=1264.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1264.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1264.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub94.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><